.TH BSTAT10S 1 "2026-04-23" "smartmet-monitor" "SmartMet Server"
.SH NAME
bstat10s \- compatibility alias for \fBbstat -i 10s\fR (ten-second buckets)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bstat10s
.RI [ \-w\  WIDTH ]
.RI [ \-\-ascii ]
.RI [ LOG-FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bstat10s
is a compatibility alias kept for operators used to the original
set of per-interval bstat functions. It calls
.B bstat
with
.B -i 10s
and forwards all remaining arguments. New scripts and
documentation should prefer
.BR "bstat -i 10s" .
.PP
Pass
.B --ascii
to render bars with the original
.B =
character instead of Unicode eighth blocks (useful for
scripts that parsed the old output or for terminals without
UTF-8 support).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bstat (1),
.BR bchart (1),
.BR burls (1),
.BR bstatus (1),
.BR bkeys (1),
.BR smtop (1)
